      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i'm looking at my mortgage statement from Wells Fargo and im a bit confused. i have a 30 year fixed at 6.5%. i want to see how much of my monthly payment is actually hitting the principal vs interest. specifically, can you show me how that looks for year 5 vs year 25? i dont need a whole spreadsheet just a general idea of the breakdown for those years.",
